Unicode Character Sets
----------------------

MySQL has two Unicode character sets. You can store texts in about 650
languages using these character sets. We have not added a large number
of collations for these two new sets yet, but that will be happening
soon. Currently, they have default case-insensitive accent-insensitive
collations, plus the binary collation.

Currently, the `ucs2_general_uca' collation has only partial support
for the Unicode Collation Algorithm. Some characters are not supported
yet.

   * `ucs2' (UCS-2 Unicode) collations:
        * `ucs2_bin'

        * `ucs2_general_ci' (default)

        * `ucs2_general_uca'

   * `utf8' (UTF-8 Unicode) collations:
        * `utf8_bin'

        * `utf8_general_ci' (default)


